data.description:
Have you heard about Vero Beach yet?  It's a fantastic place.  Picture yourself in this spectacular cozy end unit 3/3, plud den.  Town home built in 2019.  1641 sq ft 1 car garage, concrete construction, 10 foot ceiling smart house, move in ready fully furnished.  View of two  lakes.Enter into your picturesque open floor plan, bright & spacious.  Great for entertaining everyone.  Brand new premium laminate wood flooring throughout the house. Ultra-modern swanky Kitchen complete with GE Stainless steel appliances, granite countertops, farmhouse kitchen sink & white cabinetry.Downstairs bed with a full bath helps separate living quarters.  Bonus room upstairs that can be a family, cinema-room, office or den. Carmen filter water treatment system, alarm system, generator hook up. Other features include a large walk in closet, panel shutters.  UV light for allergies connected to a/c, professional painted throughout the home ceilings walls and new floor boards.  Two new fans.   
Community Low HOA Fees.  
Amenities: Lawn Care, clubhouse, exercise/fitness room, pool, tennis court, basketball court, jacuzzi spa, billiards, playground, kids room and pets allowed.  

Vero Beach is a vacation destination on the Treasure Coast with peaceful beaches, museums, art galleries, parks, and nature tours and a dog park. You can enjoy a variety of activities, such as volleyball, surfing, the beach, all water sports, fishing, walking, The pier, a cool downtown area and exploring the history and culture of the area    Some of the popular attractions include South Beach Park, McKee Botanical Garden, Pelican Island National Wildlife Refuge, Indian River Citrus Museum, Hallstrom Farmstead, McLarty Treasure Museum, Riverside Theatre, and the Vero Beach Museum of Art
Made with love for a beautiful family to come in or enjoy it all to yourself.
